Get specific data

get_waiting_time.Rd

Several functions to get specific data, such as waiting time, open encounters, current ticket number nad amount of people in a specific queue in specified office.

get_waiting_time(office_name, queue_name)

get_open_counters(office_name, queue_name)

get_current_ticket_number(office_name, queue_name)

get_number_of_people(office_name, queue_name)

Arguments

office_name

character acronym of office in Warsaw.

You can get a list of possible values using get_available_offices function.
queue_name

A character describing a queue we are interested in.

You can get a list of possible values using get_available_queues function.

Value

A character in format depending on the called function.

If get_waiting_time is called:

"Waiting time for <queue name> is x minutes".

If get_open_encounters is called:

"There are x open encounters for <queue name>".

If get_current_number is called:

"Current ticket number is x"

If get_number_of_people is called:

"There are x people in <queue name>"

Functions

  • get_waiting_time: Returns expected time to be served.

  • get_open_counters: Returns amount of opened encounters.

  • get_current_ticket_number: Returns current ticket number.

  • get_number_of_people: Returns number of people waiting in specified queue.

Examples

office <- get_available_offices()[1]
queue <- get_available_queues(office)

get_waiting_time(office, queue)
